snippet.textDisplay: When my grandmother used to sing in the Garhwali language, sometimes the Torwali sounds like that (I'm from the mountain too). The older generation definitely had a richer and heavier accent than the current generation. Also, it depends on which type of subdialect you speak, what is your medium of education, etc. When I first heard this guy, he reminded me of my dadi immediately. If fellow Garhwali people watching this, can you hear the similarity too?
